# Steps

Progress indicator for multi-step flows.

## Basic Usage
### Steps
Show progress across steps.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="StepsStepsDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxSteps :active="1">
      <TxStep title="Start" description="Collect basics" :step="0" />
      <TxStep title="Details" description="Fill in details" :step="1" />
      <TxStep title="Finish" description="Review and submit" :step="2" />
    </TxSteps>
  </template>
---
:::
## API (Lite)
### TxSteps Props
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: active
    type: "number | string"
    default: '0'
    description: Active step
  - name: direction
    type: "'horizontal' | 'vertical'"
    default: "'horizontal'"
    description: Layout direction
  - name: size
    type: "'small' | 'medium' | 'large'"
    default: "'medium'"
    description: Step size
---
:::

### TxStep Props
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: title
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Step title
  - name: description
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Step description
  - name: step
    type: "number | string"
    default: 'child order'
    description: Step identifier; child order index is used when omitted
  - name: status
    type: "'wait' | 'active' | 'completed' | 'error'"
    default: "'wait'"
    description: Manual status
  - name: clickable
    type: boolean
    default: 'true'
    description: Whether pointer/keyboard activation can switch to this step
  - name: disabled
    type: boolean
    default: 'false'
    description: Disable step interaction
  - name: icon
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Custom step icon
  - name: completedIcon
    type: string
    default: "'check'"
    description: Completed step icon
---
:::

## Interaction Contract

- When `step` is omitted, `TxStep` uses its child order as a zero-based index aligned with numeric `active`.
- Clickable step heads expose `role="button"` and `tabindex="0"`; the current step exposes `aria-current="step"`.
- Click, Enter, and Space switch the internal active step; disabled or `clickable=false` steps ignore interaction.
- The last step does not render a connector line.

